00:17:19,714 --> 00:17:22,075
I think we should discuss it before we commit dollars to it.

243
00:17:26,077 --> 00:17:30,739
I would also further think that the mailer needs to make it quick.

244
00:17:30,899 --> 00:17:35,542
Like lots of people are pulling, googling what's a high school cost.

245
00:17:36,302 --> 00:17:42,345
And I think they have an answer, but all the other high schools are just high schools, skipping the vocational conversation of it.

246
00:17:43,108 --> 00:17:51,990
We're not just a high school, we're a pile of city services that happen to be located in the building that aren't in any of these other high schools that people make access to.

247
00:17:52,030 --> 00:18:04,354
So I think this is a comprehensive high school, that means the vocational programming, the non-vocational programming, and then it's also a pile of other things that are not high school at all.

248
00:18:05,134 --> 00:18:12,796
And having that conversation one person at a time, it's exhausting, I'm sure we've all had that conversation.

249
00:18:14,222 --> 00:18:15,483
and it'd be helpful to have it.

250
00:18:16,183 --> 00:18:19,244
Don't ask me how you communicate all that on a postcard.

251
00:18:19,545 --> 00:18:27,748
It's a lot, but I would hope that we could at least also communicate this is not just the high school.

252
00:18:27,948 --> 00:18:30,069
And I think that's actually a really important message.

253
00:18:32,070 --> 00:18:39,293
I would, my recommendation would be to receive MSBA's feedback on what's reimbursable and what's not.

254
00:18:40,273 --> 00:18:42,574
So that, you know, when we word the mailer,

255
00:18:43,085 --> 00:18:49,428
We have that knowledge and we don't indicate the things which are not reimbursable.

256
00:18:50,049 --> 00:18:59,233
Many of these community amenities are in fact part of the MSBA reimbursement proposition to us, right?

257
00:18:59,253 --> 00:19:00,974
That's their value proposition.

258
00:19:02,115 --> 00:19:06,737
If you conform to our standards and follow our process, we'll share the cost with you.

259
00:19:07,417 --> 00:19:12,400
And there's aspects of our project that may not be reimbursable and you and I,

260
00:19:12,883 --> 00:19:18,304
probably already know what those are, but it's not real until the feedback arrives.

261
00:19:18,904 --> 00:19:20,605
So let's wait until the feedback arrives.

262
00:19:20,885 --> 00:19:24,186
We have the document and then we'll proceed with the mail.

263
00:19:43,515 --> 00:20:00,204
being sufficiently informed as to the scope, the extent, that I wouldn't say that people are conversant, knowledgeable about and so on, especially if they're going to be asking me to make a decision around financial impacts.

264
00:20:02,185 --> 00:20:03,786
And this is something we've talked about.

265
00:20:04,386 --> 00:20:13,331
The committee has, and I just read some of it now, all the information is on the website, it can be looked at, but the committee tends to want

266
00:20:13,761 --> 00:20:15,201
the community come to you.

267
00:20:16,382 --> 00:20:20,803
I am an advocate of you going out to the community.

268
00:20:20,903 --> 00:20:33,367
It's one of the most effective ways to go out to different school districts at those locations physically and meet with groups of people, answer their questions, have a two-way dialogue.

269
00:20:33,847 --> 00:20:35,148
That hasn't been going on.

270
00:20:35,788 --> 00:20:40,229
So I think, do people know about this project going on?

271
00:20:40,910 --> 00:20:41,230
Yes.

272
00:20:41,290 --> 00:20:42,110
Do they understand?

273
00:20:42,808 --> 00:20:46,751
the implications of it, not comprehensive.

274
00:20:46,851 --> 00:20:50,213
So I think it is more of an issue.

275
00:20:51,014 --> 00:20:51,994
That's my view.

276
00:20:52,295 --> 00:20:53,696
Can I just ask you to come forward?

277
00:20:54,116 --> 00:20:59,479
Just the people on Zoom aren't going to be able to hear you in the back, and it makes it really hard for them to know what's going on.

278
00:20:59,519 --> 00:21:02,802
The idea is that I think our library is a community center.

279
00:21:03,462 --> 00:21:10,407
I agree, it should go out to the schools, but the community library, they should have some big posters as to

280
00:21:10,857 --> 00:21:15,879
possible developments, of course, talking with the librarians to find out, but they have so much space.

281
00:21:16,019 --> 00:21:25,882
I think they would give it and allow to know what's going on, what are the options and when it should be plotted and completed and all this, you know, a timeline.

282
00:21:25,962 --> 00:21:27,342
Thank you.

283
00:21:30,403 --> 00:21:30,663
Karen?

284
00:21:31,992 --> 00:21:41,857
I attended one of the MSBA's roundtables in late November of last year, and they talked a lot about the general recommendations or standards that most communities will follow in communication out to the community.

285
00:21:41,877 --> 00:21:43,618
One of the recommendations was a mailer.

286
00:21:43,638 --> 00:21:52,302
They said that this is generally for folks in the public who may not have access to technology or may not use it commonly, who generally are more used to kind of word of mouth interaction.

287
00:21:52,702 --> 00:21:56,624
They found that this is one way to, I think, start to reinvigorate the interest.

288
00:21:56,684 --> 00:21:58,965
And I think many people in the community have mentioned that

289
00:21:59,271 --> 00:22:03,273
there is an understanding that it's happening, but maybe not more than you want components of it.

290
00:22:03,293 --> 00:22:07,836
And I think that, you know, we've been doing this for quite a while now as a committee.

291
00:22:07,856 --> 00:22:11,538
And so it's a little bit easier for us to understand what's going on because we've been doing it ourselves.

292
00:22:11,578 --> 00:22:23,065
And so I think that, you know, as we get closer and closer to these final decisions, community members are starting to want to learn more, but may not know exactly what touch points to hit upon or which members of the community to reach out to that they may know from other circles.

293
00:22:24,195 --> 00:22:25,356
For me, I'm supportive of the mailer.

294
00:22:25,476 --> 00:22:34,083
I appreciate Luke's perspective about what is the actual intention of it and how do we get that information across in the most succinct way in a short, maybe six by nine mailer.

295
00:22:35,164 --> 00:22:45,112
But I'm not quite sure about, we have the time right now, given what we're trying to accomplish in this timeline that we've already set to discuss the specifics and the language of reuse and then do that.

296
00:22:45,192 --> 00:22:50,336
I think we can make the decision we want to do it and then discuss the language and work together to find that.

297
00:22:50,497 --> 00:22:51,778
But I'm not sure we want to do that first.

298
00:22:58,719 --> 00:23:06,181
you do something like this, so it doesn't feel like we're outside the recommendations of the partner we're working with.

299
00:23:06,501 --> 00:23:06,762
Mayor?

300
00:23:07,122 --> 00:23:08,782
Thank you, Chair Graham.

301
00:23:09,382 --> 00:23:14,684
I do agree we need a mailer, if not two, one coming down the line with price tags.

302
00:23:14,724 --> 00:23:18,985
But I think if it leads to the website, that's really important.

303
00:23:19,065 --> 00:23:23,967
And I don't think there's anything stopping our designers or our OPM from

304
00:23:24,470 --> 00:23:30,332
flying carbon copying it to everybody on the committee for feedback before it goes out without having to meet him, meeting a meeting.

305
00:23:31,292 --> 00:23:40,794
So I think we can move for approval, but make sure that the committee sees it one way or another through people that won't break over meeting violation.

