00:26:17,310 --> 00:26:18,250
Jenny Graham, yes.

349
00:26:18,310 --> 00:26:19,351
Mayor Wendell Carter, yes.

350
00:26:20,012 --> 00:26:20,132
Yes.

351
00:26:20,152 --> 00:26:20,472
Yes.

352
00:26:20,552 --> 00:26:20,612
Yes.

353
00:26:20,652 --> 00:26:20,872
Yes.

354
00:26:21,193 --> 00:26:21,313
Yes.

355
00:26:21,353 --> 00:26:21,433
Yes.

356
00:26:21,453 --> 00:26:21,533
Yes.

357
00:26:50,561 --> 00:26:51,621
Onto the main event.

358
00:26:52,222 --> 00:26:52,542
Yes.

359
00:26:52,562 --> 00:27:02,048
I did get some feedback from people online that absolutely nobody who doesn't come sit up here is being heard online.

360
00:27:02,108 --> 00:27:02,269
Okay.

361
00:27:02,289 --> 00:27:08,713
So for everyone in the room, we're going to need to join us temporarily here at the table so people can hear you.

362
00:27:10,274 --> 00:27:10,554
Okay.

363
00:27:10,594 --> 00:27:11,235
Thank you for that.

364
00:27:12,536 --> 00:27:12,816
Okay.

365
00:27:12,856 --> 00:27:15,117
I'm going to turn it over to the project team.

366
00:27:15,858 --> 00:27:18,920
The thing that we are here to do tonight as a reminder,

367
00:27:19,622 --> 00:27:27,069
is to make some choices that bring our field of consideration from 29 options down to three to five.

368
00:27:28,930 --> 00:27:36,157
So the project team has prepared some information about all the various ways we've received community input so far.

369
00:27:37,518 --> 00:27:38,539
And we'll go through that.

370
00:27:38,659 --> 00:27:44,284
And then we'll also share the straw poll that we agreed to at our last meeting as a starting point.

371
00:27:45,629 --> 00:28:04,993
I also just want to reiterate that the reason we're making this down selection now is because it was the request of the MSBA so that they could focus their energy and effort on a deeper level of feedback on this important project on a smaller number of options rather than trying to sort of spread all 29.

372
00:28:06,533 --> 00:28:09,354
So we don't yet have feedback from the MSBA, but that is

373
00:28:10,616 --> 00:28:18,360
that is forthcoming and they are awaiting this decision of our three to five so that they can provide that feedback.

374
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:25,222
I'm going to turn it over to the project team who's going to take us through some slide about all the community input we have received so far.

375
00:28:27,123 --> 00:28:27,764
Thank you, Jenny.

376
00:28:28,724 --> 00:28:35,087
I'm just going to give a quick reminder as to the different types of engagement that we've had, both because

377
00:28:36,377 --> 00:28:44,701
just a good to have reminder of what we did, but also for folks that have maybe not been engaged throughout the process, just have an understanding holistically of what we've been able to run through.

378
00:28:44,721 --> 00:28:48,342
And so it's taken a variety of forms.

379
00:28:48,422 --> 00:29:00,707
There was a good level of effort associated with the community workshops and the staff workshops that happened about two or three weeks ago now in terms of timing, but we tried to approach it in a variety of ways.

380
00:29:01,868 --> 00:29:02,228
We did

381
00:29:02,792 --> 00:29:13,261
solicit priorities in the form of both some pom-poms that were identified in terms of being located in a variety of jars, as well as write-in priorities as well.

382
00:29:13,421 --> 00:29:21,788
If the prescribed priorities that were listed out that we've heard organically from the process were not listed amongst them.

383
00:29:22,589 --> 00:29:28,934
We've had some activities that focused on looking at adjacencies for the overall building design in the program.

384
00:29:29,736 --> 00:29:33,239
both within the building and then outside the building as well in terms of site program.

385
00:29:34,199 --> 00:29:52,812
And then we actually did some activities that involved opportunities to look at the overall scale and scope of the program for the project and how it would fit on the site in the form of two-dimensional and three-dimensional models that we had available at both the staff and community workshops.

386
00:29:55,034 --> 00:30:13,346
Additionally, we've handed out at all these activities that we've been doing some voice and vision cards, which allow everyone to provide us more direct input, not prescribed, but really provide us any type of feedback that's going to be on people's minds after they're engaging with the different workshop activities.

387
00:30:13,366 --> 00:30:19,390
And then we solicited feedback on the different alternatives that were out there, the 29 different alternatives.

388
00:30:20,275 --> 00:30:23,077
In the form of heat maps really of interest.

389
00:30:23,378 --> 00:30:27,321
I'm using color dots that have been distributed at various points throughout the process.

390
00:30:27,341 --> 00:30:34,866
So we have compiled all the data that we've gotten through all these various engagement methods and we want to share that first with everyone today.

391
00:30:34,927 --> 00:30:39,610
And then as Jenny mentioned, we're going to shift over to results of the straw polls.

392
00:30:40,931 --> 00:30:44,514
So first to just cover the input that we got from the voice and vision cards.

393
00:30:45,172 --> 00:30:51,697
These were the small, small postcard type cards that were handed out and really we solicited feedback on.

394
00:30:52,137 --> 00:30:59,182
What we've done is gone through and used some character recognition and some AI to synthesize the feedback that we've gotten there.

395
00:30:59,762 --> 00:31:02,504
And we've created some high-level takeaways from that.

396
00:31:02,704 --> 00:31:09,389
We will have available on the website all the individual data responses that we got in case people want to dig into those.

397
00:31:09,429 --> 00:31:14,432
But what we're trying to do is pull out trends and overlapping interests where we've seen them.

398
00:31:15,186 --> 00:31:24,531
Um, so just very quickly, um, we've broken them out, uh, from the different groups that we solicited feedback from, um, this one that's up on screen now is, uh, feedback that we've gotten from staff.

399
00:31:25,472 --> 00:31:31,816
Um, and again, we've broken this out into groupings here, um, in terms of just overlapping drivers that we saw emerge.

400
00:31:32,696 --> 00:31:40,881
Um, there's definitely a focus, um, on work environment facilities that one would expect from staff, um, from, um,

401
00:31:41,627 --> 00:31:45,948
There's a focus on student support as well and having that connected to CTE excellence.

402
00:31:46,988 --> 00:31:54,310
And also a focus on operations and logistics in terms of how the site operates, drop off traffic activity on site.

403
00:31:54,910 --> 00:32:00,852
And so I think these were as expected, it certainly aligns with what we've heard anecdotally from staff throughout the process.

404
00:32:01,732 --> 00:32:08,294
One of the particular items on the work environment facilities is this notion of class ownership and the notion that

405
00:32:08,779 --> 00:32:11,381
teachers own their classrooms here today.

406
00:32:11,441 --> 00:32:12,341
They don't move around.

407
00:32:12,821 --> 00:32:22,387
And that is it's certainly been a challenge in terms of having people be acclimated to the MSBA process where that's not an allowable model as we move forward.

408
00:32:22,407 --> 00:32:25,669
What we're trying to do is make sure that the building can be as efficient as possible.

409
00:32:26,629 --> 00:32:28,090
So it's something that's changing over.

410
00:32:28,130 --> 00:32:37,876
So this is this is not solving any of the issues as we have them displayed up here but it's really identifying what we've heard and letting us focus on those particular topics as we move forward.

411
00:32:38,384 --> 00:32:39,944
in terms of thinking about the design.

412
00:32:41,765 --> 00:32:43,145
Just big picture takeaways.

413
00:32:43,205 --> 00:32:45,646
I'm going to try to not delve into too much detail here.

414
00:32:45,686 --> 00:32:53,168
There is a lot of wonderful detail that we've heard from all these different groups but we do want to make sure that we save time to get to the deliberation on the different alternatives.

415
00:32:53,188 --> 00:32:55,789
So I'm going to try and give high level overviews here.

416
00:32:56,629 --> 00:33:04,951
On the community side again sort of the grouping of the feedback that we got was really centered around public resources and the school as a community hub.

417
00:33:05,698 --> 00:33:14,583
this notion of the neighborhood impact and also the sustainability of the building overall, as well as academic excellence in the priorities.

418
00:33:14,643 --> 00:33:16,984
And so that's important that it's coming from the community as well.

419
00:33:17,004 --> 00:33:23,808
That's not just high school staff or students, that's really the outside vision and perception of what the school really represents.

420
00:33:24,748 --> 00:33:32,872
And so you can see also here some particular topics that re-emerged, preservation of the pool, gym, and vocational shops as these public assets.

421
00:33:34,463 --> 00:33:39,945
ensuring academic spaces and teacher needs are prioritized in some cases over athletic or extra facilities.

422
00:33:39,965 --> 00:33:46,287
So in that case there's some competing senses of what the community is giving us feedback on.

423
00:33:46,387 --> 00:33:48,728
And that'll continue as we go through the process.

424
00:33:50,488 --> 00:33:58,871
From the parents that submitted the voice and vision cards again the groupings here were around student well-being and athletics.

425
00:33:59,980 --> 00:34:09,384
The notion of the safety commute and campus flow, again, this focus of site circulation, drop off and leaving the site as well.

426
00:34:10,185 --> 00:34:18,669
As well as, again, this focus on specialized academic programs and spaces, which includes this highlight of CTE being connected to that.

427
00:34:19,689 --> 00:34:25,972
And again, this covers a range of topics from modernizing sports facilities, again, focused on the gym and pool.

428
00:34:26,937 --> 00:34:33,340
ensuring safe biking and walking routes and these dedicated spaces, again, for early childhood, CTE and the arts.

429
00:34:34,761 --> 00:34:37,142
Can I make a comment before we start the next section?

430
00:34:37,182 --> 00:34:38,163
Sure.

431
00:34:38,523 --> 00:34:45,326
I just want to make an observation that these are responses from maybe 120 individuals, but we're a city of 60,000, 45,000 or 40,000 are probably adults.

432
00:34:45,346 --> 00:34:46,107
We did talk about a mailer earlier,

433
00:34:55,018 --> 00:34:57,700
And we don't have to discuss it, but I just wanna float an idea.

434
00:34:58,800 --> 00:35:04,884
These were the important thoughts and concerns from the self-selected respondents, right?

435
00:35:05,984 --> 00:35:06,945
But not the whole community.

436
00:35:07,585 --> 00:35:15,290
Would there be a way through the mailer to conduct a straw poll of what's important for the community?

437
00:35:15,330 --> 00:35:24,615
If we're gonna spend money to reach out to 40,000 people, one piece of value that we could extract out of it

438
00:35:25,232 --> 00:35:31,074
is learning what the community wants and what the community thinks is important in a new high school.

439
00:35:32,114 --> 00:35:33,415
So just food for thought.

440
00:35:33,875 --> 00:35:34,195
Thank you.

441
00:35:34,996 --> 00:35:39,297
And just to maybe respond to that, I think it is completely viable to do something like that.

442
00:35:39,397 --> 00:35:44,659
We've already have created electronic versions of those voice and vision cards.

443
00:35:45,419 --> 00:35:51,941
So we can include a link to that as part of the mailer that goes out so that people can fill that out electronically and get it back to us.

444
00:35:52,002 --> 00:35:53,282
I think the advantage there also

445
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:58,241
is that we have also multiple language translations, so it can get out to a wider variety of people.

446
00:35:59,101 --> 00:36:07,823
And then we can take that in and perform the same type of analysis that we've done on it with a smaller sample size with that larger group in terms of the feedback.

